                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18151025-12-off66 t18151025-12-crimeloc68"></join>, on the 5th of October, at about noon. I turned round, and found the prisoner at the bar, in the custody of an officer as I suppose, with my handkerchief in the prisoners hand. I did not feel it go from my pocket.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18151025-12-person142">
                  JOHN 
                  RAIN
               <interp inst="t18151025-12-person142" type="surname" value="RAIN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18151025-12-person142" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18151025-12-person142" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . On the 5th of October, I was going along Leadenhall street, and observed the prisoner walking very close to the prosecutor. At last I saw him draw the handkerchief out of his pocket. I ran across the way, and secured him. I told the gentleman, and then took the prisoner into custody.</p>
